.TH nfrm "" "" "Commands"
.PC "Display from and subject lines of new mail messages"
\fBnfrm [\-hnQqSv] [\-s\ \fIstatus\^\fB]\fR [\fIfolder \fB| \fIusername\^\fB] ...\fR
.PP
Command
.B nfrm
reads the
.B From
and
.B Subject
lines from every new message in a mailbox or folder.
It is identical to the command
.DM
	frm -s new
.DE
.PP
For details on the command-line options that this command recognizes,
see the Lexicon entry for
.BR frm .
.SH "See Also"
.B
commands,
elm,
frm,
mail (overview)
.DE
